  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "FEMALE PERSONAL TRAINER",
  "description": "<h2>Job Overview</h2><p>Avante Gym & Yoga is looking for a dedicated and professional Female Personal Trainer to join our team. This role is ideal for trainers who are passionate about helping clients improve their strength, confidence, and overall health in a safe and supportive environment.</p><h2>Key Responsibilities</h2><ul><li><p>Conduct personal training sessions for female clients</p></li><li><p>Design customised workout programmes based on clients’ goals and fitness levels</p></li><li><p>Guide clients on proper exercise techniques and injury prevention</p></li><li><p>Monitor progress and adjust training plans accordingly</p></li><li><p>Provide motivation, encouragement, and accountability</p></li><li><p>Maintain a clean, safe, and professional training area</p></li><li><p>Build strong client relationships and promote long-term retention</p></li><li><p>Follow gym policies and uphold Avante Gym & Yoga service standards</p></li></ul><h2>Requirements</h2><ul><li><p>Certified Personal Trainer (ACE, NASM, ISSA, NCSF or equivalent)</p></li><li><p>Prior personal training experience preferred (fresh trainers may apply)</p></li><li><p>Strong communication and interpersonal skills</p></li><li><p>Professional, reliable, and client-focused</p></li><li><p>Passion for women’s health, fitness, and wellness</p></li><li><p>CPR / AED / First Aid certification is an advantage</p></li></ul><h2>What We Offer</h2><ul><li><p>Competitive remuneration (basic + commission / session-based)</p></li><li><p>Supportive and friendly work environment</p></li><li><p>Access to gym and yoga facilities</p></li><li><p>Opportunity to grow your client base with strong gym & studio support</p></li><li><p>Flexible working arrangements</p></li></ul>",
